article.description: Jennifer Warkenthien had 14 points and 14 rebounds to help South Dakota State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) rout North Dakota State 70-36 on Saturday for its 12th straight victory.
article.headline: South Dakota State holds North Dakota State to season low
article.linkText: No. 18 South Dakota State wins 12th straight
article.story:
FARGO, N.D. -- Jennifer Warkenthien had 14 points and 14 rebounds to help South Dakota State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) rout North Dakota State 70-36 on Saturday for its 12th straight victory.

Warkenthien also had four assists and two steals for the Jackrabbits (26-2, 15-1 Summit League), who held the Bison (12-12, 10-6) to a season-low point total.

Maria Boever and Stacie Oistad scored 10 points apiece for South Dakota State, which has beaten the Bison eight straight games.

Jerri Penley was the only North Dakota State player in double figures with 12 points.
